 on larger scales, consistent with merger-driven models of\nquasar origin. Although our sample alone is insufficient to detect evolution in\nquasar clustering on small scales, an $i$-selected DR6 KDE quasar catalog,\nwhich will contain several hundred $z \\leqsim 5$ binary quasars, could easily\nconstrain any clustering evolution at $R_{prop} \\sim25\\kpch$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 21 Sep 2007 16:55:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-05-29"}
